                <h1>The Evolution of Anxiety: A Brief History</h1>
                <p>Anxiety has been a part of human experience for centuries, documented as far back as ancient Greece. Early philosophers like Hippocrates described anxiety, linking it to bodily imbalances. In the 20th century, psychological research advanced, with Freud introducing the concept of anxiety as a key symptom of mental illness. Today, anxiety disorders are recognized as common mental health conditions, shaped by both genetic and environmental factors.</p>
